&lt;p&gt;About the job&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ProSkill Services is seeking experienced HVAC Service Technicians who take pride in their work and are passionate about customer service. Do you like being a part of a winning team? Are you tired of working hard while others are skating by?&amp;nbsp; Are you looking to take your career and earning potential to the next level? If this sounds like you, and your workmanship and customer service are second to none, we want to talk to you!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver exceptional customer service and acting in the customer&#39;s best interest at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct maintenance and repair: Perform preventive maintenance for new and existing customers, respond to on demand service calls for down HVAC systems..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inventory Control: Maintain your service van tock according to company SOP, ensuring that you are properly stocked for your day to day operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety and compliance: Follow all workplace and driving safety standards and regulations, to maintain a safe working environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation: Document service performed and recommendations made by completing applicable forms, reports, logs, and/or records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications And Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant HVAC training program or apprenticeship is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: Minimum of 3 years of experience as an HVAC technician.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Licenses: Valid driver’s license, and EPA certification. NATE certification and Master Heat Pump Technician a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skills: Strong technical knowledge, excellent problem-solving abilities, attention to detail, and effective communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical Requirements: Ability to work in various conditions, including confined spaces and at heights; physical stamina and dexterity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hourly Pay + Performance Incentives, spiffs, and commissions when applicable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;93&quot; data-end=&quot;124&quot;&gt;Sign-On Bonus: Up to $7,500&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Eligible candidates may receive a sign-on bonus of up to $7,500, subject to company policies and qualifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health Coverage: Comprehensive benefits - Medical, Dental, Life, Vision insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K retirement plan with partial company match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company-provided iPhone and iPad&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uniforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid vacation and holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully equipped company truck with parts, equipment, and gas card (For Qualified Positions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training &amp;amp; Development: Continuous education and advancement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company Culture: Supportive, inclusive, and team-oriented work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work Environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Works in field environments across residential job sites, climbing ladders and navigating uneven surfaces. Regularly works in confined spaces and moves materials up to 50 pounds. Operates hand and power tools and vehicles. Must be able to see, hear, and exchange accurate information with customers and team members. Regular exposure to outdoor weather, noise, and dust. Reasonable accommodations may be made to perform essential functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
